Place a #pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the @vegetable gyoza{10} and fry until golden on all sides, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn carefully to avoid tearing.

Add a splash of @water{to taste}, cover and cook for another ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once cooked, remove from the pan and cover to keep warm.

Meanwhile, place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Trim the @green beans{100%g}.

Once the pan is hot, add the green beans and fry until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add the @sesame oil{20%ml} and a splash of @water{to taste} and cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}.

Cook until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Remove the pan from the heat.

Meanwhile, mix the @aioli{1%sachet}, @gochujang paste{1%sachet} and @honey{2%sachet} in a #bowl{}.

Divide the gyoza and green beans between plates.

Serve with sauce alongside for dipping.

> This perfectly portioned snack or side features veg gyoza accompanied by a spicy gochujang aioli.